{"sections":[{"projectFiles":"OUDS-Onboarding-Tutorial.zip","image":"ic_unified_ds.png","xcodeRequirement":"Xcode 26.4","backgroundImage":"ic_unified_ds.png","kind":"hero","chapter":"Import of the Swift Package and choose its librairies","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS iOS is exposed through an open source Swift Package hosted on GitHub, and provides several librairies for your needs.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"These librairies help to split products and make users able to select only what they need.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"SwiftUI is the only official supported framework for Apple platforms.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"estimatedTimeInMinutes":10,"title":"Swift Package integration"},{"kind":"tasks","tasks":[{"stepsSection":[{"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using Xcode, in your "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"project package dependencies","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", add a new "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"dependency","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Search with the GitHub repository URL (https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios), and select the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"ouds-ios","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" dependency."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can then choose the "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"dependency rule","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" you want."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To know which version you need, you can have a look on the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/wiki\/01-%E2%80%90-Available-API"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and also the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/releases"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":"tutorial-onboarding-1-ouds-swift-package.png","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s say you will use the some beta version, here 1.3.0-beta.2"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":null},{"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once you downloaded the package, you will see several librairies are available."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"They can be embeded inside your "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"target","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" librairies."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Things are separated to let users integrate only what they need and embed the abre minimum of content."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesContract","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" library provides the main elements like the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSThemeableView"},{"type":"text","text":". The theme contract is defined inside it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesOrange","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesSosh","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Sosh products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesWireframe","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Wireframe theme, which is a theme dedicated to mockups and prototypes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesOrangeCompact","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products but with constraints of sizes and spaces."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSComponents","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" contains the SwiftUI OUDS components defined with the Figma specifications, and also useful view modifers."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSTokensRaw","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSTokensSemantic","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSTokensComponents","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" are librairies defining and providing the tokens for low level (raw),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"middle level (semantic) or component levels (high level)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSModules","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is for modules or rich components with extra logic."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSFoundations","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is dedicated to some utilities and shared logic."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":"tutorial-onboarding-1-ouds-libraries.png","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add for example only the umbrella product merging all products mentioned above: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSSwiftUI","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":null}],"title":"Import the Swift Package and the libraries","anchor":"Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries","contentSection":[{"kind":"contentAndMedia","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS for iOS is an open source Swift Package available on GitHub under MIT license."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The package and the librairies must be added through Xcode."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"mediaPosition":"trailing"}]}]},{"kind":"assessments","anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding","assessments":[{"choices":[{"isCorrect":true,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"I can contribute to OUDS using pull request"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS is open source, under MIT license, and hosted on GitHub. Of course you can contribute!"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"isCorrect":false,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS supports officialy all Apple OS like visionOS, tvOS, watchOS, iPadOS, iOS and also CarPlay."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The main supported targets are iOS \/ iPadOS. However we do our best to support macOS, visionOS, tvOS and watchOS."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"CarPlay specific cases are not scoped yet."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"isCorrect":false,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS provides UIKit components"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS supports only SwiftUI."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"title":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Which of these choices is correct?"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[],"type":"multiple-choice"},{"choices":[{"isCorrect":true,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some of the available products depending to my needs, or only "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSSwiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":" if I am very lazy and don’t care about my app size."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can import all products provided by the Swift Package, and tailor your choice to keep only the ones needed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Even if we recommend to choose only the atomic products you need, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSSwiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":" product wraps all of them."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"isCorrect":false,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"None, only the Swift package dependency matter."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need to chose the products the Swift package provides."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"title":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Which imports of the OUDS Swift Package products can I choose?"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[],"type":"multiple-choice"}]},{"featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial","kind":"callToAction","action":{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get started"}],"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Get started","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-2-nice-and-clear-view","type":"reference"},"title":"Define information cards","abstract":[{"text":"Let’s suppose we want to define a view for corporate apps with headings, texts, buttons and images.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"How can we do that?","type":"text"}]}],"hierarchy":{"modules":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)\/Import-of-the-Swift-Package-and-choose-its-librairies","projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-1-package-and-librairies","sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-1-package-and-librairies#Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries"},{"kind":"assessment","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-1-package-and-librairies#Check-Your-Understanding"}]}]},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)\/Define-information-cards","projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-2-nice-and-clear-view","sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThem